        <p>
          A good meeting is more than just a few people talking to each other in
          a room. For efficient meetings you need to set an agenda, people need
          to prepare, notes and conclusions need to be shared, and follow-up
          discussion need to be captured, organized, and fostered. In short:
          meetings are a synchronous exchange but efficient meetings are wrapped
          in asynchronous communication.
        </p>
